snippet.textDisplay: Anything can be fashionable... Anything can be trendy... But not everything is functional, comfortable or fits well on every body type...The only thing that limits how fashionable a single item of clothing may be is the lack of items to pair and accessorize it with to complete a look... You put a $5 pair of oversized jeans on a celebrity paired with the right top, shoes, accessories and take pictures of them at the right angles and everyone will love it... Hence why big designer brands can sell you clothes for hundreds or thousands of dollars that only take a couple dollars worth of material and couple dollars worth of labor to make... What you pay for is the marketing not the quality of the product sadly...
